name: [ Lo tuyo, lo mío y la mitad ]
description: Agave Karwinskii | [ Lo tuyo, lo mío y la mitad ] We heard a story about this agave: the cuixe is a tall agave so people in the towns of Oaxaca use it as a kind of natural fence to separate their lands, delimiting "What is yours, what is mine and half". Part of the NFT pieces of the series “Memorias Orgánicas” a work of exploration and registration through 3D scanning on endemic natural elements of Oaxaca, Mexico. | 1080 x 1080 px | http://f3.studio/portfolio/mo/ | IG: @f3.output TW: @F3_STUDI0
